# Coding Conventions

## Language
All code, comments, XML docs, annotations, and repository content must be in **English**.

## Documentation Requirements
- Every class MUST have a `/// <summary>` (2-4 lines): responsibility, key dependencies, how it fits in the system
- Public methods MUST have `/// <summary>`, with `<param>` and `<returns>` when applicable
- Files over 300 lines MUST use `#region` to group methods by category
- Inspector fields MUST use `[Header("Category Name")]` for visual grouping

## Naming
- PascalCase: classes, methods, public properties
- camelCase: private fields
- Enums: PascalCase for type and values
- Do NOT use C# reserved keywords as identifiers (e.g. `base`, `class`, `ref`, `out`, `in`)

## Prefabs and asset naming (new content)
- **Do not rename** existing prefab files or asset filenames in the project for consistency with this rule — only apply conventions to **new** assets and variants.
- **Slope / zoning / building variants** (see `SlopePrefabRegistry`, `.cursor/specs/isometric-geography-system.md` §6.4): use the pattern `{flatPrefabName}_{slopeCode}Slope` where `slopeCode` is one of `N`, `S`, `E`, `W`, `NE`, `NW`, `SE`, `SW`, `NEUp`, `NWUp`, `SEUp`, `SWUp`.
- **Roads, terrain, UI:** follow existing prefixes in each folder (e.g. `roadTilePrefab*`, `northSlopePrefab`); new prefabs should mirror the established naming style in that category.

## Dependency Pattern
```csharp
[Header("Manager References")]
[SerializeField] private GridManager gridManager;

void Awake() {
    if (gridManager == null) gridManager = FindObjectOfType<GridManager>();
}
```

## Anti-patterns to Avoid
- Do NOT create new singletons — use Inspector + FindObjectOfType pattern
- Do NOT access `gridArray` or `cellArray` directly from outside GridManager — use `GetCell(x,y)`
- Do NOT use `FindObjectOfType` in Update/loops — only in Awake/Start
- Do NOT add more responsibilities to GridManager — extract to helper classes

## Reference Files
- Documentation model: `EconomyManager.cs` (XML docs + regions + headers)
- Region model: `Cell.cs` (4 well-named regions)
